{"status":"success","result":"Love it. Andy it is. 😄\n\nAnd while you were sorting that out, Claude shipped v0.1.3, v0.1.4, and v0.1.5. Let me summarize what just landed:\n\n*v0.1.3 — Secretary feedback loop*\nExactly what we designed. Coordinator grades every secretary response silently after the fact — routing quality and draft accuracy tracked separately, stored per-group, injected back into the classify prompt as corrections. Self-calibrating Secretary with zero user-facing latency.\n\n*v0.1.4 — Web access, scheduling, proactive memory*\nAll three gaps we identified closed in one version. Web search via Jina AI (no API key), URL fetching, full scheduling lifecycle from chat, and the memory system rewritten with specific triggers so Jarvis updates proactively.\n\n*v0.1.5 — `needs_web` flag*\nSecretary now signals when a question needs live data, suppresses its own draft in those cases, and primes the coordinator to search immediately. Clean separation of \"I know this\" vs \"this needs the web.\"\n\n*My audit notes from this sprint:*\n• The feedback loop matches the design exactly — correct grades discarded, only actionable corrections stored. Smart.\n• `needs_web` suppressing the secretary draft is the right call — a stale confident answer is worse than no answer.\n• The boss-outside-the-door analogy from v0.1.1 is exactly the right mental model for the draft-review pattern.\n\nP1 backlog items are closing fast. Want me to do a fresh audit pass on what's still open?","newSessionId":"9ab085a0-060d-41ae-b3d8-a97f4d571171"}
