{"status":"success","result":"Good. That's the full definition of experience quality for this project:\n\n*Quality of life* — does it make the user's day better, not just functional\n*Intuitiveness* — does it behave the way you expect without explanation\n*Ease of use* — is the path to the outcome short and clear\n*Reliability* — does it do what it's supposed to, every time\n*Responsiveness* — does it feel alive and present, not laggy or dead\n\nThese five should be the evaluation criteria for every Jarvis feature — not just \"does it work\" but \"does it feel right.\" They're also a useful lens for the error taxonomy: a behavioral error often violates intuitiveness, an environmental error violates reliability, a slow escalation chain violates responsiveness.\n\nWorth adding these explicitly to the testing philosophy doc as the definition of a passing experience — not just test coverage, but the bar the experience has to clear.\n\nShall I draft the full document now?","newSessionId":"9ab085a0-060d-41ae-b3d8-a97f4d571171"}
